==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪ|-aɪ]]

=== Adjective ===
'''wry'''
#(''of humour'') [[dry]] and [[sardonic]] or [[ironic]]
# [[twisted]] to one side, or [[crooked]]
# [[perverse]]

==== Example ====

* The wry telephonist character played by [[w:Lily Tomlin|Lily Tomlin]] made a point of using an obscure [[phonetic alphabet]].  "Did you say apple?  A as in Aardvark, P as in Psychic, another P as in Palindrome ..."

'''wry definition''' 

# A definition of a word made using its homonyms and synonyms.  Examples:
** A [[trio]] of [[pear]]s [[pare]]d to a [[pair]] of [[pear]]s.
** The price of the [[fare]] at the [[fair]] was [[fair]].

